name: you look bangin'
description:
mustaches, beards, ironic facial hair, we've seen it all. but what's the lady trademark of hipness? that's easy. BANGS! long, beautiful bangs!

let someone know your thinking about how bangin' they look by giving them this bangin' card chock full of bangy goodness. BANG!

it measures 5 x7 inches when folded, and comes with a chartreuse envelope.

PS, it's my original illustration, of my bangs.

name: Screen Printed Jersey Scarf in Heather Blue with White Peacock Feather Print

Oh, how I love American Apparel's tri-blend fabrics! They're 50% Polyester / 25% Cotton / 25% Rayon, which makes them super soft, with that vintage tee shirt feeling.

This scarf is made up of a 93" x 16" piece of said fabric in athletic blue. I printed my peacock feathers design on each end in white. Then I heat set the ink, making it safe to wash and wear over and over again! It's the perfect lightweight, year-round scarf, and I'm not just saying that because I made it.


(since they are printed by hand, the placement of the design can vary slightly, but it will be awfully close to the photo!)

what better way to flatter your mom than through the classic means of a pick up line?!

name: way to go
description:
Reasons why this is an awesome card:

1. It has a cool background design, I call doodletron, printed in poppin' chartreuse. It's a really cool way to congratulate a graduate, pat a retiree on the back or give props to your crazy marathon-running pal.


2. You can also use it in a sarcastic way. For the person who blew the promotion, accidentally backed their car into their garage, or lost their eyebrows in an overzealous ronsonol backyard fire-starting.
(Don't be mean about it though.)

p.s.
it's a folded card that measures 4.25 x 5.5 inches when folded, is blank inside, and comes with a recycled paper bag envelope (100% recycled).

name: I done fell in love with you
description:
Sometimes its hard to use your real voice to tell someone you love them. Being sincere is tricky. Give me something serious to say and I turn into a Cockney barmaid.

So pretend you have bad grammar, let your jaw go a little slack, and say "I done fell in love with you." Because that's what being a mature adult is all about.

this card measures 5 x 7 inches when folded, has rounded corners and comes with a curry yellow envelope.

name: LIKE card
description:
People are always talking about love this time of year. Well what if you just started dating someone on say, January 29th? You'd feel obligated to express something come valentine's day, but you don't want to get carried away. Enter the Like card.

The design is a parody of Robert Indiana's famous "LOVE" sculptures. So you'll be all "I like you, and I'm clever." Win, win!!

It's a folded card that measures 4.25 x 5.5 inches and is printed on 20% cotton paper, finished with rounded corners. Envelope is gravel gray.

name: H to your B Day
description:
Who has time to spell out entire phrases these days? What with the veritable slew of friends you have to give cards to. Shorten things up. "H to your B day" sounds cool. Like I want to wish you a happy birthday, but I'm not going to spend all day doing it, because I'm important...and that's why you love me.

Or maybe it just sounds cute...and is printed all nicely with my feathers and rustic stencil pattern in the background. And maybe you like cute sounding things? And pretty looking things, who doesn't like them?

Either way, this 5 x 7 folded card is sure to please someone, somewhere, somehow!

name: Don't let the Dingo take your baby
description:
As a person who knows about dingos and their affinity for babies, its your job to keep the new parents on their toes. Make everyone a little uncomfortable with this mildly threatening new baby card!

measures 4.25 x 5.5 inches when folded and comes with a recycled brown bag envelope.

name: Lurve Card
description:
If you're a fan of Annie Hall, you know just what I'm talking about:

"Do you love me? Love is too weak a word. I lurve you. You know, I
lo-ove you. I luff you. There are two "f's." I have to invent... of
course I love you."

Awww.... so sweet. And then I combined the sentiment with a parody of Robert Indiana's famous "LOVE" sculpture. Could this valentine be any more cerebral? Finally, the perfect card for the smart and in lurve.

It's a folded card that measures 4.25 x 5.5 inches and is printed on 20% cotton paper, finished with rounded corners. Envelope is gravel gray.

name: your baby is cute squared times infinity
description:
they're going to believe you no matter what.

this card measures 4.25 x 5.5 inches when folded and comes with a pale yellow envelope.

it's a wedding card!

name: I LOVE YOU, MOM
description:
I LOVE YOU, MOM

that's all you really have to say to melt your mom's butter.

I made this design up of layers of scanned doilies that were made by my grandma. Sweet, right?! It's printed on a textured Italian paper that's 20% cotton. Schmancy! And it's paired with an embossed metallic envelope in a light and lovely gold.

The card measures 5 x7 when folded and is blank inside.

name: sorry I'm not an elephant-belated birthday or something
description:
....because elephants never forget, get it? Smarmy elephants with their photographic memories. I'm sure it's easy to never forget anything when you're just standing around all day drinking water out of your nosemouth.

anywho! this card is perfect for anything you've forgotten...a birthday, an anniversary (gasp!), a dry cleaning pick up....the list goes on. remember: everything is forgettable!

name: tanks-thank you card
description:
you know, "tanks!" it's what my grandma used to say as a cute thank you. more fun and interesting than "thanks." be more fun and interesting!

this card measures 4.25 x 5.5 inches when folded and is printed on a light cement gray cardstock. Coordinating envelope is chartreuse.

name: I can't see anything that I don't like about you
description:
what a nice thing to say! any valentine worth their salt is gonna love this.

AND...if that valentine is at all into the movie Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind, you might get some extra bonus points for being clever:

Joel: I can't see anything that I don't like about you.
Clementine: But you will! But you will. You know, you will think of things. And I'll get bored with you and feel trapped because that's what happens with me.
Joel: Okay.
Clementine: [pauses] Okay.

this card measures 5 x 7 inches when folded and comes with a peacock (teal) envelope.

name: happy wedding time

it's a wedding card!

name: you're a good egg-single folded card
description:
my grandma always used to say "i like her. she's a good egg." or "well sure, but he's still a good egg."

So for me, being a good egg is pretty much the best thing to be ever. In fact, I can't think of a nicer thing to say to someone. So, if you need to let someone know that they're a real, salt-of-the-earth type individual, pick up this card and let it do the talking for you.

It's a folded card that measures about 4.25 x 5.5 inches and is printed on lovely textured white card stock. It comes with a coordinating 4.25 x 5.5 envelope in natural kraft, which is 100% recycled. It's digitally (flat) printed.
